<doc id="1002033" wikidata="Q1759688" url="?curid=1002033" title="Cafelândia, São Paulo">
<text>Cafelândia is a municipality of the state of São Paulo in Brazil. The population is 17,843 (2020 est.) in an area of . The elevation is .

== Media ==
In telecommunications, the city was served by Companhia Telefônica Brasileira until 1973, when it began to be served by Telecomunicações de São Paulo. In July 1998, this company was acquired by Telefónica, which adopted the Vivo brand in 2012.

The company is currently an operator of cell phones, fixed lines, internet (fiber optics/4G) and television (satellite and cable).

